<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-29T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-29T04:00:00-05:00" n="248" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P. W./343: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-29T18:00:00+09:00">July 29,
                                    1941—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 29—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1118. My 1103, July 27, 7 p.m. During a talk today the Chief of the
                            American Bureau of the Foreign Office informed Dooman that the Foreign
                            Office had received a very brief telegram from Admiral Nomura concerning
                            the President’s proposal but he characterized the report as being too
                            brief to be of any use and said that the Minister had instructed Nomura
                            by telegraph on Sunday afternoon, July 27, to submit promptly a
                            comprehensive report.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>